  <refnamediv>
    <refname>colon (:)</refname>
    
    <refpurpose>Affects a variable in Maxima</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    
    <para>The Scilab operator colon (:) is overloaded for sym variables at the left side to affect a Maxima variable in Maxima environment.</para>
      
  </refsection>

  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    
    <programlisting role="example">
x=sym('x'),y=x*x
x:3,y

//You can kill a variable
kill(x),y 
    </programlisting>
  </refsection>
  
